# OZONE STUDIO — Complete Production-Ready Modifications Guide v2.0

## DECISIONS CONFIRMED

1. **Context Aggregation**: Both (Pipeline #21 for external + orchestrator internal)
2. **Chunk→Modality Graph**: Yes, `provenance = DerivedFromChunk`, nodes reference source
3. **File Attachments**: Process during prompt normalization (Phase 1)
4. **Unknown Modality**: Both (generic container + META clarification via ZSEI self-review)
5. **Cross-Ref Storage**: Separate cross-modal index, both graphs reference
6. **Engine UI**: Both supported (engine-embedded OR headless + separate UI)

---

## PART 1: CROSS-CUTTING CHANGES (ALL Modalities 100–123)

### 1.1 Universal Edge Types

```rust
// Add to EVERY modality's edge type enum:
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize, PartialEq)]
pub enum EdgeType {
    // === EXISTING STRUCTURAL EDGES ===
    Contains,
    ContainedBy,
    ParentOf,
    ChildOf,
    Precedes,
    Follows,
    HasAttribute,

    // === SEMANTIC INFERENCE (Grammar/Action-Verb Derived) ===
    Performs,           // Subject performs action on object
    Affects,            // X affects Y (causal)
    Implies,            // X implies Y (logical)
    Contradicts,        // X contradicts Y
    Elaborates,         // X elaborates on Y
    Summarizes,         // X summarizes Y
    Supports,           // X supports claim Y
    TemporalPrecedes,   // X happens before Y
    TemporalFollows,    // X happens after Y
    CausedBy,           // X was caused by Y
    Enables,            // X enables Y
    Prevents,           // X prevents Y
    PartOf,             // X is part of Y
    HasPart,            // Y has part X
    FunctionalRole,     // X serves function in Y
    InstanceOf,         // X is instance of Y (type)
    HasInstance,        // Y has instance X
    SimilarTo,          // X similar to Y
    RelatesTo,          // Generic relationship

    // === PROVENANCE (Source Object Tracking) ===
    DerivedFrom,        // X was derived from Y
    VersionOf,          // X is version of Y
    RefinesTo,          // X refines/improves Y
    ForkedFrom,         // X was forked from Y

    // === CROSS-MODALITY ===
    ReferencesModality, // Text references modality content
    ReferencedBy,       // Modality referenced by text
    DescribedBy,        // X described by Y (usually text)
    Describes,          // X describes Y
    ImplementedIn,      // X implemented in Y (usually code)
    Implements,         // X implements Y
    VisualizedAs,       // X visualized as Y (image/3D)
    Visualizes,         // X visualizes Y
    SyncedTo,           // Temporal sync (audio↔video)
    SyncedBy,           // Reverse sync
}
```

